    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CANADA TO SELL OIL COMPANY</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Canada will sell its remaining 18 percent stake in Petro-Canada, country's second-largest integrated oil company and eliminate 25 percent limit on foreign investment in company (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Canada will sell its remaining 18 percent stake in Petro-Canada, the country's second-largest integrated oil company, and eliminate a 25 percent limit on foreign investment in the company. At current market prices, the government's holding is worth about $1 billion. The government, which created Petro-Canada in 1975, sold most of its shares in the early 1990's.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard (NYT)</p>
      </block>
